Richard Beauchamp, Lord Bergavenny, married Isabel, who by the death of her brother Richard had become heiress of Glamorgan, and was in ward to the Crown, They were married 27th July, 12 Henry 1V., 1411, and he had livery of her lands ‘2 Henry V. He was created Earl of Worcester 1420, and died 18th March, 1422. This Charter therefore was granted seven years after he had had livery‚ ten months before

his death, ten days after that to the burgesses of Car-diff, and on the same day with that to the burgesses of Neath.
